@ebarboni thanks! Yes, same reason I insisted on having a separate link for plugins in 11.1 despite it directing to same location as 11.0 currently - more flexibility to switch things around as we need.

I think 8.2 is mainly there for C/C++ support now.  But as and until we're sure we're dropping from the next release I think we should keep in master too.  Particularly with the release work you're looking at, the less changes needed between master and release112 the better!

I manually retriggered Travis tests which passed second time around - Travis seems to be having issues with us again today!

Hi @peedeeboy,

I have tested Payara/GlassFish server registration from Maven, Gradle, and Ant web project and found no issue so far except missing localization bundle warning in Ant Web project.

@neilcsmith-net, Yes I am aware of Payara Micro ergonomics issue and I will fix it in upcoming next week. But it should only disable the Payara Micro application and must not have any impact on Payara Server tooling.

@one-leaf Did you read this? https://netbeans.apache.org/participate/submit-pr.html 
You should create a branch.
Did you read @lkishalmi 's comments? https://github.com/apache/netbeans/pull/1416#pullrequestreview-273455218

@neilcsmith-net @jGauravGupta just to say that I tested this by cloning a fresh copy of master, then fetching this PR and building NB from that branch.  

So I do think enabling Payara getting stuck on "Activating feature is unrelated to this PR itself, and as Neil's suggests is because I didn't have an ergonomics fix locally - I don't think it should hold up this PR.. ?

Hope that helps :)

@jmborer if you are looking for a binary, you can get this one: https://doppel-helix.eu/netbeans-dev.zip That is the build I'm currently using at work. it is based on commit 39e97b900a8d604f3968e07605ee0d7709f37977 with PR #1417. The timeframe is totally ok.

@junichi11 the PRs intentend change is visible, when you run a maven project, that has an integration test defined. This is a sample project:
[testTests.zip](https://github.com/apache/netbeans/files/3506166/testTests.zip)
Open it, run the custom goal "integration-test" and open the test-results window. You will see one output with the unittest (on current netbeans), however, when you look at the console, you see that there are in fact two tests run (one unittest, one integration test).
With this PR, a second test results window is opened, that shows the integration test.
